For {= charity_year =}+ Australian registered charity reporting years with official ACNC AIS dataset-row values, supply {= financial_report_kmp_note =}+ audited financial-report KMP remuneration note or same-purpose disclosure per charity-year, with {= url =}+ URL for the audited annual financial report or financial statements.

When this subtask is run with its ACNC AIS parent, it is the audited-report side of the same charity-year set, not a separate report inventory. Every child row should match a root AIS row on charity name or reporting entity, ABN or ACNC group ABN, reporting year, `fin_report_from`, and `fin_report_to`. A child row is useful in a composite answer only when the matching official AIS row is also sourceable.

Composite pair discipline: this child file does not count by itself, and a large root block does not compensate for child underfill. In a composite run, maintain one private pair ledger and also emit the root `results_acnc_kmp_consistency.jsonl` block for official AIS dataset rows before this child block. The two blocks should use exactly the same `charity_name`, `abn`, `reporting_year`, `fin_report_from`, and `fin_report_to` values for the paired charity-year set, preferably in the same row order. Emit at least {= charity_year =} root AIS rows and at least {= charity_year =} child audited-report rows, with a modest paired surplus when practical. Do not add unpaired root or child surplus until at least {= charity_year =} matched pairs are present; if output budget becomes tight, preserve at least {= charity_year =} exact matched pairs before adding surplus to either file. A final answer with one block only, fewer than {= charity_year =} root rows, fewer than {= charity_year =} child rows, or materially different root and child charity-year sets is incomplete.

Hard paired-output gate for composite answers: every child object must have a matching root object with the same `charity_name`, `abn`, `reporting_year`, `fin_report_from`, and `fin_report_to`, and every root object must have a non-empty official AIS row `url`. Never use `url: null`, omit the root URL, or put the audited report URL in the root block. If a candidate has a child report but no official AIS row URL, discard it or find the AIS row before emitting either row. If a candidate has an AIS row but no audited-report KMP note, discard it or find the audited report before emitting either row. Root-heavy and child-heavy answers both fail.

Emit-ready replacement pass: raw root/child key alignment is necessary but not sufficient. Before final output, count a pair only when the root artifact visibly returns the exact AIS row and the child artifact is a direct audited-report PDF/download or official report page whose visible text is the audited report itself. The root artifact must expose literal returned values for `Key Management Personnel`, `Number of Key Management Personnel`, and `Total paid to Key Management Personnel` in the same official datastore JSON record or downloaded CSV row used for the key. Replace, rather than submit, any singleton root-only or child-only key, broad `q=` or ABN-only datastore URL that does not show the exact period and all three KMP fields, landing/index page such as annual reports, publications, or finances, ACNC register shell, document list, impact-only or unaudited page, or paraphrased/synthetic report excerpt. Do not submit a short draft merely because the keys align; continue collecting until at least {= charity_year =} emit-ready matched pairs remain, with paired surplus as the target.

Output discipline: the final response must prioritize compact JSONL records over explanation. Do not include methodology, progress notes, tables, rankings, or narrative summaries. Keep each child record concise: one audited-report URL, one or two short excerpts that quote only the report identity and KMP note/amount/exemption text, and only the fields needed for `charity_year`, `financial_report_kmp_note`, the comparison class, and the amount/unit evidence. Short supported child rows are better than a smaller set of long child rows. Do not stop at a partial set below {= charity_year =} pairs when more paired charity-years are available.

Standalone child-only volume note: when this child node is run without the ACNC AIS parent, produce at least 300 candidate financial-report records, and overproduce beyond that when practical, so that at least {= charity_year =} distinct charity-years survive deduplication and judging. A standalone child file with fewer than {= charity_year =} accepted distinct charity-years is incomplete, and a file with no cushion above {= charity_year =} candidates is likely underfilled after deduplication and judging.

Composite root source rule: when you emit the required root `results_acnc_kmp_consistency.jsonl` block, cite official AIS row artifacts such as `data.gov.au/data/api/3/action/datastore_search` row URLs with datastore resource UUIDs, official ACNC/data.gov.au resource API responses, or downloaded official AIS CSV row text. A compact ABN-filtered URL with a small `fields=` projection is preferred but not required. The root evidence must visibly contain the exact charity row: ABN or group ABN, charity name, financial-report dates, and KMP fields. Do not write `resource_id=acnc-2024-annual-information-statement-ais-data`, `resource_id=acnc-2023-annual-information-statement-ais-data`, or similar package slugs in a datastore-search URL; those are package slugs, not resource UUIDs. Known high-yield AIS resource UUIDs are `cfbcf6f1-7ce5-472f-bfd3-a478e67e0366` for 2022 AIS rows, `2b0fb746-57c5-4523-bb4c-74b7b78279d9` for 2023 AIS rows, and `710630ea-1202-4bbb-95f7-3973a972ddf8` for 2024 AIS rows. A broad package/resource landing page without row-level values does not satisfy the root block unless the cited artifact or quoted downloaded row text includes the submitted row.

Composite AIS row workflow:
- Do not let either block outrun the other. Keep a private paired list and emit a child row only after the official AIS row has been checked for the same ABN or group ABN and reporting period; likewise, emit a root row in a composite answer only after the direct audited-report KMP note has been checked for that same charity-year.
- For the root row in a composite answer, use `https://data.gov.au/data/api/3/action/datastore_search?resource_id=<AIS_RESOURCE_UUID>&filters={"abn":"<ABN_WITHOUT_SPACES>","fin report from":"<DD/MM/YYYY>","fin report to":"<DD/MM/YYYY>"}&limit=1` or equivalent official row text. Quote the returned `abn`, `charity name`, `fin report from`, `fin report to`, `Key Management Personnel`, `Number of Key Management Personnel`, and `Total paid to Key Management Personnel` fields from the official record. Copy those AIS KMP values verbatim into `ais_kmp_count` and `ais_total_paid_to_kmp`; do not fill them from the financial report.
- The child row should reuse the exact root `charity_name`, `abn`, `reporting_year`, `fin_report_from`, and `fin_report_to`. If the audited report period or entity scope cannot be reconciled to that official AIS row, discard the pair and move to another charity-year.

ABN-only root URLs are unsafe for charities with multiple AIS years. Do not rely on an `abn`-only `limit=1` datastore response unless the returned record visibly matches the submitted financial-report dates and all three KMP fields. Prefer a period-specific datastore filter, a downloaded official CSV row, or quoted row text that includes the exact `fin report from` and `fin report to`. If the row's KMP count or total differs from the JSON/excerpt, update the root/child pair to the returned AIS row values or discard the pair; never import annual-report KMP values into the root AIS fields.

AIS-first verification rule for composite answers: the root block must be based on actual official AIS row data before any child report row is emitted. Check that the source returns or quotes a record whose ABN or group ABN, charity name, `fin report from`, `fin report to`, and KMP fields match the root JSONL item and excerpt. If the source returns no row, a different financial-report period, or different KMP values, discard the candidate or change the root/child pair to the exact returned AIS row and then find an audited report for that same reporting period. Do not infer root AIS dates or KMP values from the audited report.

Composite root returned-field extraction gate: when emitting the root block from this child task, copy AIS KMP fields exactly as the official row returns them. `Number of Key Management Personnel` and `Total paid to Key Management Personnel` must be present as explicit returned values, including literal `0` values for true zero/no-remunerated-KMP cases. Do not turn null, blank, missing, or invisible AIS KMP fields into `No`, `0`, or financial-report values. If the AIS artifact returns no row, the wrong ABN, a different financial-report period, any missing/blank KMP field, or KMP values that cannot be quoted exactly, discard the whole pair before writing either block. A child report cannot rescue a fabricated or coerced root AIS row.

The financial-report evidence should identify the audited report URL, note/page/table reference, amount and unit/scale, column or comparative year, count if disclosed, scope notes, and a neutral comparison class against the ACNC AIS dataset-row values for the same reporting period. Emit a child row only when the paired AIS row has exact returned numeric evidence for both the KMP count and total paid fields; a no-remunerated-KMP pair still needs explicit AIS zero values plus report wording that supports the zero/no-remunerated state.

Each child JSONL row should include the neutral comparison fields the judge needs, not only the key fields:
```json
{"charity_name":"...","abn":"...","reporting_year":"2024","fin_report_from":"01/07/2023","fin_report_to":"30/06/2024","financial_report_note_reference":"Note ... Key management personnel compensation, page ...","financial_report_column_year":"2024","report_entity_scope":"...","financial_report_amount":"...","financial_report_unit_scale":"whole dollars or $000 or explicit no-remunerated-KMP wording","financial_report_kmp_count":"...","ais_kmp_count":"...","ais_total_paid_to_kmp":"...","comparison_class":"exact_match","url":"https://...","excerpts":["report title/entity and period or comparative-column context","note/table heading; 2024 and 2023 column headers; unit/scale; total KMP remuneration row or explicit no-remunerated-KMP wording"]}
```

Paired batch workflow: work in batches of 20-40 charity-years and close each candidate into an exact pair before moving on. You may start from either official AIS rows or audited financial reports, but report-led batches are often more efficient for child evidence: find a direct audited report or financial-statements PDF with a KMP/related-party note, then verify the official AIS row for that same ABN or ACNC group ABN and period. Do not emit a child record unless the audited report clearly matches the same charity, ACNC group, branch, consolidated scope, or controlled-entity scope and the same reporting period returned by the AIS row. Multi-year audited reports with comparative columns are high-yield: the same official report URL may support adjacent charity-years only when excerpts quote the note/table label, both year or comparative column headers, and the unit/scale for the claimed column. After each batch, continue with a new set of charities rather than expanding narrative.

Efficient report route: search exact charity name plus "financial statements", "annual financial report", "key management personnel", "related parties", and the reporting year. Prioritize direct audited PDF URLs or official annual-report pages from the charity, parent reporting entity, or ACNC-hosted document downloads. Annual-report index pages and ACNC register document pages are acceptable discovery surfaces, but the cited child URL/excerpt must resolve to the audited financial report PDF/download or quote the downloaded report text itself; a generic register shell, document list, product page, impact-only report, unaudited summary, or page without KMP/related-party note text is not enough.

Wrong-entity report reuse is a hard fail. Do not cite one charity's audited report and rename it as another charity. Before emitting a child row, verify that the cited PDF or report page itself names the same charity, ACNC group, branch, parent/consolidated reporting entity, or controlled-entity scope as the submitted `charity_name`/`abn`, and that it covers the same reporting period or comparative column. If the report title/entity/scope does not visibly reconcile to the AIS row, discard the pair.

Excerpt support matters. Use compact excerpts, but make them complete. One excerpt should identify the audited report title/entity or scope and the report period or comparative column. Another excerpt should identify the KMP/related-party note heading or table label, exact column year, unit/scale (`$`, whole dollars, `$000`, thousands, no-remunerated-KMP wording, or exemption wording), and total KMP remuneration amount or exemption/no-KMP wording. A bare line with only a number is not enough even when the full PDF contains the right table.

Child financial-report self-audit before final output: for every child row, verify that the quoted excerpts alone show the audited report entity/scope, the report period or comparative column used for the AIS charity-year, the KMP/related-party note heading, the exact column year, the unit/scale, and the total KMP remuneration amount or explicit no-remunerated-KMP/single-KMP-exemption wording. Discard rows whose excerpt is only a heading, only a number, a donations/director-interest row, a governance roster, or a directors-only statement that conflicts with a positive aggregate KMP amount elsewhere in the note. If the report period, entity scope, column year, amount, count, or scale does not match the AIS row, do not call it `exact_match` or `no_remunerated_kmp`; use the appropriate neutral class such as `amount_conflict`, `count_conflict`, `scope_mismatch`, `timing_year_mismatch`, `financial_report_only_amount`, or `not_comparable`, and quote the text that makes that class clear.

Final paired-table gate: keep a private table of more than {= charity_year =} candidate charity-years and submit at least {= charity_year =} fully verified pairs, with paired surplus when practical, whose root AIS row and child financial-report row both pass their support checks. Count a pair only if the root excerpt quotes nonblank returned AIS values for `Key Management Personnel`, `Number of Key Management Personnel`, and `Total paid to Key Management Personnel`, and the child excerpt includes report title/entity or scope, report period or comparative column, note/table heading, exact column year, unit/scale, amount or explicit no-remunerated-KMP/exemption wording, and a comparison class supported by those excerpts. If fewer than {= charity_year =} pairs survive this audit, continue collecting new charities and reports rather than submitting a short, root-heavy, or child-heavy answer.

Comparison classes are: `exact_match`, `rounding_or_000_scaling_match`, `ais_only_amount`, `financial_report_only_amount`, `count_conflict`, `amount_conflict`, `scope_mismatch`, `timing_year_mismatch`, `no_remunerated_kmp`, `single_remunerated_kmp_exemption`, and `not_comparable`.

This is a source-alignment task. Do not describe rows as misconduct, noncompliance, donor advice, compensation advice, pay fairness, rankings, or controversy unless an official regulator source says that for the specific entity and period. Individual CEO pay is not required; aggregate KMP remuneration is usually the relevant disclosure.

Source validity note:
- The cited page should be an audited annual financial report or audited financial statements for the claimed charity, ACNC group, consolidated group, branch, or controlled-entity scope.

Requirements:
- The page should support the claimed report scope and the financial-report period or comparison column used for the charity-year.
- The page should state the KMP remuneration disclosure needed for the row: amount and unit/scale, no remunerated KMP, single-remunerated-KMP exemption, report-only amount, or comparable disclosed absence.
- The answer's comparison class should follow from the financial-report evidence and the claimed AIS row values, treating whole-dollar versus `$000` presentation, rounding, comparative-year columns, branch/group scope, and timing differences neutrally.
